ith were able to go to countries such as China and create mosques around 627 C. E.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.islamreligion.com/articles/11321/islam-enters-far-east/|title=Islam Enters the Far East - The Religion of Islam|last=waheed|website=www.islamreligion.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-16}}</ref> As men from the Middle East came to China they would get married to these Asian women, which led to a spreading of the faith and traditions of Islam in multiplicities.<ref name=\":1\" /> The Crusades in the 9th and 10th centuries encouraged the spread of Islam through the invasions of Latin Christian soldiers and Muslim soldiers into each other's lands. The whole conflict began on the premises of a Holy Land and which group of people owned these lands that led to these foes invading their respective lands.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.history.com/news/why-muslims-see-the-crusades-so-differently-from-christians|title=Why Muslims See the Crusades So Differently from Christians|work=HISTORY|access-date=2018-10-16|language=en}}</ref> As the religion itself spread so did its implications of ritual, such as prayer.\n\n==Sikh music==\n{{main|Sikh music}}\n\n==Jewish music==\n{{main|Jewish music}}\nThe earliest synagogal music was based on the same system as that in the [[Temple]] in [[Jerusalem]]. According to the [[Talmud]], [[Joshua ben Hananiah]], who had served in the sanctuary [[Levite|Levitical]] choir, told how the choristers went to the synagogue from the orchestra by the [[altar]] (Talmud, Suk. 53a), and so participated in both services.\n\n==Hindu music==\n{{main|Hindu music}}\n\n==Neopagan music==\n{{main|Neopagan music}}\nNeopagan music is music created for or influenced by [[modern Paganism]]. It has appeared in many styles and genres, including [[folk music]], [[classical music]], [[singer-songwriter]], [[post-punk]], [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] and [[ambient music]].\n\n==Rastafarian music==\n{{main|Rastafarian music}}\n\n==Shint\u0